.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1549,2006]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1549,1574]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Disc covered by small scales, even smaller on ventral interradius. Two lateral oral papillae, distal larger and wider than the proximal. Dorsal and ventral arm plates form overlapping series. Two tentacle scales, the one attached to the ventral arm plate rather wide. Three to five arm spines, slender and pointed (
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas, L. P." box="[1268,1432,1621,1646]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="827 - 833" part="16" refId="ref54699" refString="Thomas, L. P. (1966) A revision of the tropical American species of Amphipholis (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea). Bulletin of Marine Science, 16, 827 - 833." title="A revision of the tropical American species of Amphipholis (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea)" type="journal article" year="1966">Thomas 1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tommasi, L. R." box="[151,321,1657,1682]" journalOrPublisher="Contribuicoes Avulsas do Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 146" part="20" refId="ref54902" refString="Tommasi, L. R. (1970) Os ofiuroides recentes do Brasil e de regioes vizinhas. Contribuicoes Avulsas do Instituto Oceanografico, Universidade de Sao Paulo, 20, 1 - 146." title="Os ofiuroides recentes do Brasil e de regioes vizinhas" type="journal article" year="1970">Tommasi 1970</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Turner, R." box="[333,475,1657,1682]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1028 - 1029" part="98" refId="ref55025" refString="Turner, R. (1985) Microphiopholis, replacement name for Micropholis Thomas, 1966 (Ophiuroidea: Amphiuridae), non Huxley, 1859 (Amphibia: Dissorophidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 1028 - 1029." title="Microphiopholis, replacement name for Micropholis Thomas, 1966 (Ophiuroidea: Amphiuridae), non Huxley, 1859 (Amphibia: Dissorophidae)" type="journal article" year="1985">Turner 1985</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="35" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,1549,2006]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1693,1718]" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turner" authorityYear="1985" box="[344,530,1693,1717]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Microphiopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[344,530,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Microphiopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was suggested by 
<bibRefCitation author="Turner, R." box="[750,910,1693,1718]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1028 - 1029" part="98" refId="ref55025" refString="Turner, R. (1985) Microphiopholis, replacement name for Micropholis Thomas, 1966 (Ophiuroidea: Amphiuridae), non Huxley, 1859 (Amphibia: Dissorophidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 1028 - 1029." title="Microphiopholis, replacement name for Micropholis Thomas, 1966 (Ophiuroidea: Amphiuridae), non Huxley, 1859 (Amphibia: Dissorophidae)" type="journal article" year="1985">Turner (1985)</bibRefCitation>
to replace 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1966" box="[1042,1178,1693,1717]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Micropholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1042,1178,1693,1717]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Micropholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, formerly assigned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas, L. P." box="[151,327,1729,1754]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="827 - 833" part="16" refId="ref54699" refString="Thomas, L. P. (1966) A revision of the tropical American species of Amphipholis (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea). Bulletin of Marine Science, 16, 827 - 833." title="A revision of the tropical American species of Amphipholis (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea)" type="journal article" year="1966">Thomas (1966)</bibRefCitation>
. In accordance with International Commission on Zoological Nomenclature, a replacement name was required because more than a century earlier, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1966" box="[732,868,1765,1789]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Micropholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[732,868,1765,1789]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Micropholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was used for an amphibian taxon (
<bibRefCitation author="Turner, R." box="[1277,1424,1765,1790]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1028 - 1029" part="98" refId="ref55025" refString="Turner, R. (1985) Microphiopholis, replacement name for Micropholis Thomas, 1966 (Ophiuroidea: Amphiuridae), non Huxley, 1859 (Amphibia: Dissorophidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 1028 - 1029." title="Microphiopholis, replacement name for Micropholis Thomas, 1966 (Ophiuroidea: Amphiuridae), non Huxley, 1859 (Amphibia: Dissorophidae)" type="journal article" year="1985">Turner 1985</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turner" authorityYear="1985" box="[151,337,1801,1825]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Microphiopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,337,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Microphiopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ljungman" authorityYear="1866" box="[609,750,1801,1825]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Amphipholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[609,750,1801,1825]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Amphipholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the presence of much finer scales on the disc, which explains its name (
<bibRefCitation author="Thomas, L. P." box="[361,519,1837,1862]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of Marine Science" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="827 - 833" part="16" refId="ref54699" refString="Thomas, L. P. (1966) A revision of the tropical American species of Amphipholis (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea). Bulletin of Marine Science, 16, 827 - 833." title="A revision of the tropical American species of Amphipholis (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea)" type="journal article" year="1966">Thomas 1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Turner, R." box="[531,673,1837,1862]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1028 - 1029" part="98" refId="ref55025" refString="Turner, R. (1985) Microphiopholis, replacement name for Micropholis Thomas, 1966 (Ophiuroidea: Amphiuridae), non Huxley, 1859 (Amphibia: Dissorophidae). Proceedings of the Biological Society of Washington, 98, 1028 - 1029." title="Microphiopholis, replacement name for Micropholis Thomas, 1966 (Ophiuroidea: Amphiuridae), non Huxley, 1859 (Amphibia: Dissorophidae)" type="journal article" year="1985">Turner 1985</bibRefCitation>
). These authors suggest that only 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turner" authorityYear="1985" box="[1054,1240,1837,1861]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Microphiopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1054,1240,1837,1861]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Microphiopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a perforation in the arm vertebrae. Because this feature was also observed in other species of amphiurids and ophiotrichids (
<bibRefCitation author="Irimura, S. &amp; Fujita, T." box="[158,412,1909,1934]" editor="Feral, J. - P." journalOrPublisher="Swets &amp; Zeitlinger, Lisse" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="161 - 166" refId="ref49211" refString="Irimura, S. &amp; Fujita, T. (2003) Intraspecific variation of vertebral ossicle morphology in the Ophiuroidea. In: Feral, J. - P. &amp; David, B. (Eds.), Echinoderm Research 2001. Swets &amp; Zeitlinger, Lisse, pp. 161 - 166." title="Intraspecific variation of vertebral ossicle morphology in the Ophiuroidea" type="book chapter" volumeTitle="Echinoderm Research 2001" year="2003">Irimura &amp; Fujita 2003</bibRefCitation>
), we do not consider this character in our diagnosis. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Turner" authorityYear="1985" box="[1001,1187,1909,1933]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Microphiopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1001,1187,1909,1933]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Microphiopholis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
presently includes six species (
<bibRefCitation author="Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A." box="[247,439,1945,1970]" journalOrPublisher="PLoS ONE" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="0164562" part="11" refId="ref54292" refString="Stohr, S. &amp; Martynov, A. (2016) Paedomorphosis as an Evolutionary Driving Force: Insights from Deep-Sea Brittle Stars. PLoS ONE, 11, e 0164562. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0164562" title="Paedomorphosis as an Evolutionary Driving Force: Insights from Deep-Sea Brittle Stars" type="journal article" year="2016">
Stöhr 
<emphasis box="[316,365,1945,1969]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
) with three of them recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[838,906,1945,1970]" name="Brazil" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barboza, C. A. M. &amp; Borges, M." box="[922,1203,1945,1970]" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="1 - 21" part="3447" refId="ref44247" refString="Barboza, C. A. M. &amp; Borges, M. (2012) A checklist of the extant species of ophiuroids (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from Brazilian waters. Zootaxa, 3447, 1 - 21." title="A checklist of the extant species of ophiuroids (Echinodermata: Ophiuroidea) from Brazilian waters" type="journal article" year="2012">Barboza &amp; Borges 2012</bibRefCitation>
): 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stimpson, 1852)" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1852" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1852" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiuridae" genus="Ophiolepis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="atra">
<emphasis box="[1222,1307,1946,1969]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">M. atra</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stimpson, W." journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Boston Society of Natural History" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="224 - 226" part="4" refId="ref54058" refString="Stimpson, W. (1852) Descriptions of two new species of Ophiolepis from the southern coast of the United States. Proceedings of the Boston Society of Natural History, 4, 224 - 226." title="Descriptions of two new species of Ophiolepis from the southern coast of the United States" type="journal article" year="1852">Stimpson, 1852</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stimpson, 1852)" authorityName="Stimpson" authorityYear="1852" baseAuthorityName="Stimpson" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[230,585,1981,2006]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Microphiopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="gracillima">
<emphasis box="[230,385,1981,2005]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">M. gracillima</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stimpson, W." box="[399,577,1981,2006]" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Boston Society of Natural History" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="224 - 226" part="4" refId="ref54058" refString="Stimpson, W. (1852) Descriptions of two new species of Ophiolepis from the southern coast of the United States. Proceedings of the Boston Society of Natural History, 4, 224 - 226." title="Descriptions of two new species of Ophiolepis from the southern coast of the United States" type="journal article" year="1852">Stimpson, 1852</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ljungman, 1867)" authorityName="Ljungman" authorityYear="1867" baseAuthorityName="Ljungman" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[639,971,1981,2006]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Amphiuridae" genus="Microphiopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis box="[639,758,1981,2005]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="35">M. subtilis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ljungman, A. V." box="[772,963,1981,2006]" journalOrPublisher="Ofversigt af Konglige Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar" pageId="34" pageNumber="35" pagination="303 - 336" part="23" refId="ref50339" refString="Ljungman, A. V. (1867) Ophiuroidea viventia huc usque cognita, enumerat. Ofversigt af Konglige Vetenskaps-Akademiens Forhandlingar, 23, 303 - 336." title="Ophiuroidea viventia huc usque cognita, enumerat" type="journal article" year="1867">Ljungman, 1867</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
